    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your feedback posted on the NHS website regarding your son's experience of our Urgent Care Services, including the Walk In Centre (WIC), Emergency Department (ED) and the Acute Medical Unit (AMU).  It was kind of you to take the time to compliment the staff as it is good to receive positive feedback which reflects the hard work and dedication of our staff. 

We were sorry to learn that your sonâ€™s experience was not entirely positive as we would hope particularly in regards to the proposed transfer to another ward in the early hours of the morning. It is important to us that comments are heard as they provide an opportunity to the service to make changes and improvements. 

Where possible the aim is to transfer patients at a time and in a manner that causes as little disruption as possible to the patient but unfortunately this is not always achievable and there are occasions when patients require transfer during the night. We would like to apologise again and if you would like to discuss your experience with us in more detail, please do not hesitate to contact our Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) on 0161 276 8686 or by e-mailing pals@mft.nhs.uk quoting reference number PO18/0251.

The Patient Experience Team&lt;/CommentText&gt;
